article.description: — Dylan Penn had 18 points and 11 rebounds as Bellarmine easily defeated Asbury College 87-55 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Penn lifts Bellarmine past Asbury College 87-55
article.linkText: Penn lifts Bellarmine past Asbury College 87-55
article.story: LOUISVILLE, Ky. -- — Dylan Penn had 18 points and 11 rebounds as Bellarmine easily defeated Asbury College 87-55 on Thursday night. Ethan Claycomb and CJ Fleming added 15 points each for the Knights. Garrett Tipton had 10 points for Bellarmine (4-6). Bellarmine scored 43 first-half points, a season best for the team. Nick Fort had 13 points for the Eagles. John Shoulders added 12 points. Will O'Bryan had three points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
